The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sports

 Races postponed by a day 

 OUR TURF CORRESPONDENT

 Calcutta: In view of the proposed Bengal bandh, the Stewards of Royal Calcutta Turf Club (RCTC) have decided to postpone the city races, scheduled for Friday, by a day, according to an RCTC notification. Stewards have also advanced the first race which will start at 12 noon. Timings of the rest of the races have also been altered to accommodate the later half of the Bangalore inter-venue betting on the day.




